<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1367,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,1403,1429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Diagnosis (emended).</emphasis>
Prostomium wider than long. Two antennae; two palps similar in size/shape to antennae. No median antenna or nuchal papilla. Nuchal organs unknown. Eyes absent. Smooth proboscis, papillae at distal end. Segment 1 fused or not (dorsally) to prostomium. Segment 1 distinct ventrally. Elongated dorsal cirri (EDC) (= tentacular cirri) on segments 1, 2; EDC on segment 3. No ventral cirri on segment 1. Ventral cirri on segment 2 elongated or like following segments. Parapodia uniramous, notopodial chaetae absent. Neuropodium with central fascicle containing compound chaetae; one simple emergent acicula. Compound chaetal shaft cylindrical; pointed blade extended from falcate joint. Rostrum of chaetal shaft asymmetrical/hooked. Presence of segmental bands of cilia. Pygidial cirri robust ellipsoid lobes. Living animals are red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1367,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1692,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on this study, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[547,755,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,755,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now includes five species; 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1058,1179,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis box="[1058,1179,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1192,1365,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1192,1365,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1370,1431,1692,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,273,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,273,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[281,343,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[356,478,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="patricki" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[356,478,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. patricki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[486,548,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Blake and Hilbig" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[610,732,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verenae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[610,732,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. verenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[740,838,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A." box="[845,1012,1727,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="67 - 101" refId="ref14106" refString="Blake, J. A. (1985) Polychaeta from the vicinity of deep-sea geothermal vents in the eastern pacific. I. Euphrosinidae, Phyllodocidae, Hesionidae, Nereididae, Glyceridae, Dorvilleidae, Orbiniidae, and Maldanidae. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 6, 67 - 101." type="journal article" year="1985">Blake’s (1985)</bibRefCitation>
original 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1114,1322,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1114,1322,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
diagnosis stated that the genus has segment 1 fused dorsally to the prostomium, and no dorsal cirri on segment 3. We amend the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[192,400,1800,1826]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,400,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
diagnosis to allow for the variation shown in other members of the genus. For instance, some taxa do not have segment 1 fused to the prostomium and may have dorsal elongated cirri on segment 
<quantity box="[1269,1311,1836,1862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
addition to segments 1 and 2 (
<tableCitation box="[355,442,1872,1898]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="TABLE 4. Features of Galapagomystides species. (P) = present. (A) = absent." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" tableUuid="44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED">Table 4</tableCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel, F." box="[461,632,1872,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="225 - 261" refId="ref17152" refString="Pleijel, F. (1991) Phylogeny and classification of the Phyllodocidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta, 20, 225 - 261. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1991. tb 00289. x" type="journal article" year="1991">Pleijel’s (1991)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[779,987,1872,1898]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,987,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accepted 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A." box="[1097,1262,1871,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="67 - 101" refId="ref14106" refString="Blake, J. A. (1985) Polychaeta from the vicinity of deep-sea geothermal vents in the eastern pacific. I. Euphrosinidae, Phyllodocidae, Hesionidae, Nereididae, Glyceridae, Dorvilleidae, Orbiniidae, and Maldanidae. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 6, 67 - 101." type="journal article" year="1985">Blake’s (1985)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis, with the addition of nuchal organs present as dorso-lateral ciliated pits between the prostomium and segment 1. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel, F." pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="225 - 261" refId="ref17152" refString="Pleijel, F. (1991) Phylogeny and classification of the Phyllodocidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta, 20, 225 - 261. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1991. tb 00289. x" type="journal article" year="1991">Pleijel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
also questioned the presence of segmental ciliated bands though their presence is confirmed here. All species within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[229,437,1980,2006]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,437,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an asymmetrical/hooked tip of the chaetal shaft, which is unique to the genus among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orsted" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,315,2016,2042]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Phyllodocidae</taxonomicName>
. For a morphological summary of variation within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[888,1096,2016,2042]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[888,1096,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<tableCitation box="[1145,1235,2016,2042]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="TABLE 4. Features of Galapagomystides species. (P) = present. (A) = absent." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" tableUuid="44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED">Table 4.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
